casebody.data:
Office of Disciplinary Counsel v. Butler.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Butler (1999), 85 Ohio St.3d 1.]

(No. 98-2212 Submitted December 16, 1998 Decided March 3, 1999.) *2Jonathan E. Coughlan, Disciplinary Counsel, and John K. McManus, Assistant Disciplinary Counsel, for relator. Kegler, Brown, Hill & Ritter and Geoffrey Stem, for respondent. Per Curiam.

We adopt the board’s findings, conclusions, and recommendation. Respondent is hereby publicly reprimanded. Costs are taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
